+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01C8jhPVzY5F8to79Skef7Ke","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a complete picture of the project. Let me compile this into a comprehensive report:\n\n## Complete Project Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── events/\n│   │   ├── types.ts          # Event type definitions and constants\n│   │   └── bus.ts            # Event bus implementation (pub/sub)\n│   ├── orders/\n│   │   ├── service.ts        # Order lifecycle management\n│   │   └── repository.ts     # Order data storage\n│   ├── inventory/\n│   │   ├── service.ts        # Stock reservation logic\n│   │   └── repository.ts     # Inventory data storage\n│   ├── billing/\n│   │   ├── service.ts        # Payment processing\n│   │   └── calculator.ts     # Price calculation with discounts/tax\n│   ├── notifications/\n│   │   └── service.ts        # Order notification templates\n│   └── index.ts              # Main entry point (exports)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── orders.test.ts        # OrderService + OrderRepository tests\n│   ├── billing.test.ts       # BillingService + price calculator tests\n│   ├── inventory.test.ts     # InventoryService tests\n│   ├── notifications.test.ts # NotificationService tests\n│   └── events.test.ts        # EventBus tests\n├── Configuration Files\n│   ├── package.json\n│   ├── tsconfig.json\n│   ├── vitest.config.ts\n│   ├── .eslintrc.cjs\n│   └── TASK.md\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Package.json Configuration\n\n**Name:** bench-debug-nightmare  \n**Type:** module (ES modules)  \n**Version:** 1.0.0  \n**Description:** Event-driven order processing system — hard debugging benchmark\n\n**Scripts:**\n- `npm run build` → Compiles TypeScript with `tsc`\n- `npm run lint` → Lints `src/` and `tests/` directories\n- `npm test` → Runs tests with `vitest run`\n\n**DevDependencies:**\n- typescript: ^5.4.0\n- vitest: ^2.0.0\n- eslint: ^8.56.0\n- @typescript-eslint/parser: ^7.0.0\n- @typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin: ^7.0.0\n\n---\n\n### 3. TypeScript Configuration (tsconfig.json)\n\n- **Target:** ES2022\n- **Module System:** Node16\n- **Output:** ./dist/\n- **Root:** ./src/\n- **Strict Mode:** Enabled\n- **Features:** ES Module interop, source maps, type declarations with maps\n- **Includes:** All src/**/* files\n- **Excludes:** node_modules, dist, tests\n\n---\n\n### 4. ESLint Configuration (.eslintrc.cjs)\n\n- **Parser:** @typescript-eslint/parser\n- **Extends:** ESLint recommended + TypeScript recommended\n- **Key Rule:** `@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars` with `_` prefix exemption\n- **Environment:** Node.js with ES2022 features\n\n---\n\n### 5. Vitest Configuration (vitest.config.ts)\n\n- **Globals:** Enabled (describe, it, expect available globally)\n- **Test Timeout:** 10 seconds per test\n\n---\n\n### 6. All Source Files and Exports\n\n#### **src/index.ts** (Main Entry Point)\nExports:\n- `EventBus` class\n- `ORDER_EVENTS` constant\n- Event type interfaces: `OrderEvent`, `OrderCreatedEvent`, `OrderCancelledEvent`, `OrderRefundedEvent`, `PaymentChargedEvent`, `StockReservedEvent`\n- `OrderRepository`, `Order`, `OrderItem`, `OrderStatus`, `OrderService`\n- `InventoryRepository`, `StockRecord`, `InventoryService`\n- `BillingService`, `PaymentRecord`, `calculateOrderTotal`, `PriceBreakdown`\n- `NotificationService`, `NotificationRecord`\n\n#### **src/events/types.ts**\n**Interfaces:**\n- `OrderEvent` - Base event with orderId and timestamp\n- `OrderCreatedEvent` - Items, customerId\n- `OrderCancelledEvent` - reason\n- `OrderRefundedEvent` - amount\n- `PaymentChargedEvent` - amount, paymentMethod\n- `StockReservedEvent` - items array\n\n**Constants:**\n```typescript\nORDER_EVENTS = {\n  CREATED: 'order.created',\n  CONFIRMED: 'order.confirmed',\n  CANCELLED: 'order.cancelled',\n  REFUNDED: 'order.refunded',\n  PAYMENT_CHARGED: 'order.payment.charged',\n  STOCK_RESERVED: 'order.stock.reserved',\n  STOCK_RELEASED: 'order.stock.released',\n  NOTIFICATION_SENT: 'order.notification.sent',\n}\n```\n\n#### **src/events/bus.ts**\n**Class: EventBus**\n- Module-level global handler registry (shared across instances)\n- `on(event, handler)` - Register handler\n- `off(event, handler)` - Unregister handler\n- `emit(event, data)` - Emit event (async)\n- `clear()` - Clear all handlers\n\n#### **src/orders/repository.ts**\n**Interfaces:**\n- `OrderStatus` type: 'pending' | 'confirmed' | 'cancelled' | 'refunded'\n- `OrderItem` - productId, quantity, unitPrice\n- `Order` - Full order with id, customerId, items, status, total, discount, taxRate, timestamps, notes\n\n**Class: OrderRepository**\n- In-memory Map<string, Order> store\n- `create()` - Create order with copy\n- `findById()` - Get order by id\n- `update()` - Update with partial fields (preserves id, updatedAt)\n- `findByCustomer()` - Filter by customer\n- `findByStatus()` - Filter by status\n- `clear()` - Clear store\n\n#### **src/orders/service.ts**\n**Class: OrderService**\nConstructor: OrderRepository, EventBus, BillingService\n\nMethods:\n- `createOrder(id, customerId, items, discount, taxRate)` → Creates → emits CREATED → charges payment → emits CONFIRMED → returns Order\n- `cancelOrder(id, reason)` → Validates confirmed → emits CANCELLED → updates status\n- `refundOrder(id)` → Validates cancelled → checks 30-day refund window → issues refund\n- `getOrder(id)` → Fetch order\n- `getOrdersByCustomer(customerId)` → Fetch all for customer\n\n**Constant:** REFUND_WINDOW_DAYS = 30\n\n#### **src/inventory/repository.ts**\n**Interface:**\n- `StockRecord` - productId, available (qty), reserved (qty)\n\n**Class: InventoryRepository**\n- In-memory Map<string, StockRecord> store\n- `setStock(productId, available)` - Set available quantity\n- `getStock(productId)` - Get stock record\n- `reserve(productId, quantity)` - Reserve stock (decrement available, increment reserved) → returns boolean\n- `release(productId, quantity)` - Release reservation → returns boolean\n- `clear()` - Clear store\n\n#### **src/inventory/service.ts**\n**Class: InventoryService**\nConstructor: InventoryRepository, EventBus\n\nMethods:\n- `registerHandlers()` - Register CREATED and CANCELLED event handlers\n- `handleOrderCreated()` - Reserves stock for all items, emits STOCK_RESERVED, rolls back on failure\n- `handleOrderCancelled()` - Releases stock, checks status !== 'cancelled', emits STOCK_RELEASED\n- `setStock(productId, quantity)`\n- `getStock(productId)`\n\n#### **src/billing/calculator.ts**\n**Interface:**\n- `PriceBreakdown` - subtotal, discountAmount, taxAmount, total\n\n**Function: calculateOrderTotal(items, discountPercent, taxRate)**\n- Calculates subtotal (sum of quantity × unitPrice)\n- Applies percentage discount\n- Applies tax on discounted amount\n- Returns PriceBreakdown with all amounts rounded to 2 decimals\n\n#### **src/billing/service.ts**\n**Interface:**\n- `PaymentRecord` - orderId, amount, method, status ('charged'|'refunded'), processedAt\n\n**Class: BillingService**\nConstructor: EventBus, NotificationService\n\nMethods:\n- `registerHandlers()` - Register STOCK_RESERVED and REFUNDED event handlers\n- `handleStockReserved()` - Emits PAYMENT_CHARGED event\n- `chargePayment(orderId, items, discountPercent, taxRate, paymentMethod)` - Calculates total, creates PaymentRecord, sends confirmation notification\n- `handleRefund()` - Updates payment status to 'refunded', sends refund notice\n- `issueRefund(orderId, amount)` - Updates status, emits REFUNDED event\n- `getPayment(orderId)` - Fetch payment record\n- `clear()` - Clear payments\n\n#### **src/notifications/service.ts**\n**Interface:**\n- `NotificationRecord` - type, orderId, message, sentAt\n\n**Class: NotificationService**\nConstructor: Initializes template map with 3 templates\n- 'order.confirmed' → \"Your order {orderId} has been confirmed. Total: ${total}\"\n- 'order.cancelled' → \"Your order {orderId} has been cancelled. Reason: {reason}\"\n- 'order.refunded' → \"Your refund of ${amount} for order {orderId} has been processed.\"\n\nMethods:\n- `sendConfirmation(orderId, total)` - Sends confirmation with template substitution\n- `sendCancellation(orderId, reason)` - Sends cancellation notice\n- `sendRefundNotice(orderId, amount)` - Sends refund notification\n- `getSentNotifications()` - Returns copy of all sent records\n- `clear()` - Clear sent notifications\n\n---\n\n### 7. All Test Files (30 Visible Tests)\n\n#### **tests/events.test.ts** (5 tests)\nTests EventBus functionality:\n1. ✓ Emits events to registered handlers\n2. ✓ Supports multiple handlers for same event\n3. ✓ Does not fire handlers for different events\n4. ✓ Removes handlers with off()\n5. ✓ Clears all handlers\n\n#### **tests/orders.test.ts** (12 tests)\n**OrderService Tests (10):**\n1. ✓ Creates an order and confirms it (status=confirmed, total=55)\n2. ✓ Reserves stock when order is created (available=7, reserved=3)\n3. ✓ Cancels a confirmed order (status=cancelled)\n4. ✓ Releases stock when order is cancelled (available=10, reserved=0)\n5. ✓ Refuses to cancel a non-confirmed order (returns undefined)\n6. ✓ Refunds a cancelled order within 30 days (status=refunded)\n7. ✓ Allows refund on exactly day 30 (status=refunded)\n8. ✓ Rejects refund after 30-day window (throws error)\n\n**OrderRepository Tests (2):**\n9. ✓ Creates and retrieves an order\n10. ✓ Updates order preserves other fields\n11. ✓ Returns undefined for missing order\n12. ✓ Finds orders by customer (finds by customerId)\n\n#### **tests/billing.test.ts** (8 tests)\n**calculateOrderTotal Tests (4):**\n1. ✓ Calculates total with no discount or tax (100)\n2. ✓ Applies percentage discount before tax (97.2)\n3. ✓ Handles multiple items with discount and tax (130.86)\n4. ✓ Rounds correctly for penny-edge amounts (33.88)\n\n**BillingService Tests (4):**\n5. ✓ Charges payment and records it (amount=110, status=charged)\n6. ✓ Sends confirmation notification on charge (type=confirmation)\n7. ✓ Issues refund and updates payment status (status=refunded)\n8. ✓ Sends refund notification (refund type, includes amount)\n\n#### **tests/inventory.test.ts** (5 tests)\n1. ✓ Reserves stock on order.created (available=7, reserved=3)\n2. ✓ Throws when stock is insufficient (error: \"Insufficient stock\")\n3. ✓ Rolls back partial reservations on failure (SKU-1 available=10, reserved=0)\n4. ✓ Releases stock on order.cancelled (available=10, reserved=0)\n5. ✓ Reserves stock for concurrent orders independently (available=12, reserved=8)\n\n#### **tests/notifications.test.ts** (4 tests)\n1. ✓ Sends order confirmation (type=confirmation, contains orderId and amount)\n2. ✓ Sends cancellation notice (type=cancellation, contains reason)\n3. ✓ Sends refund notice (type=refund, contains amount)\n4. ✓ Tracks all sent notifications (length=3)\n\n---\n\n### 8. Key System Characteristics\n\n**Event-Driven Architecture:**\n- Central EventBus with global handler registry\n- 8 event types define the order lifecycle\n- Services register handlers to react to events\n- Async event emission with sequential handler execution\n\n**Order Lifecycle:**\n1. **Create** → order.created → inventory reserves stock → billing charges → order.confirmed\n2. **Cancel** → order.cancelled → inventory releases stock\n3. **Refund** → order.refunded (within 30-day window)\n\n**State Management:**\n- In-memory repositories using Map<string, T>\n- Immutable copies returned from repository methods\n- Shared event bus across all service instances\n\n**Business Rules:**\n- 10% default tax rate on orders\n- 30-day refund window from order creation\n- Discount applied before tax calculation\n- Stock reservation with rollback on failure\n- Decimal precision to 2 places for currency\n\n---\n\nThis is a comprehensive event-driven order processing system with well-defined modules, clear separation of concerns, and complete test coverage across 30 visible tests spanning event handling, orders, inventory, billing, and notifications."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a98668d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 32189\ntool_uses: 25\nduration_ms: 39380</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b51607b8-49ee-45e0-91aa-5308df462f0a","uuid":"d3ddb9ee-b130-4097-bda0-bd9b94cdd918","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the project structure at /workspace thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The full directory tree (src/ and tests/)\n2. All source files and their exports\n3. The package.json scripts and dependencies\n4. The tsconfig and eslint configuration\n5. All test files and what they test\n\nGive me the complete picture of every file in the project.","agentId":"a98668d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a complete picture of the project. Let me compile this into a comprehensive report:\n\n## Complete Project Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── events/\n│   │   ├── types.ts          # Event type definitions and constants\n│   │   └── bus.ts            # Event bus implementation (pub/sub)\n│   ├── orders/\n│   │   ├── service.ts        # Order lifecycle management\n│   │   └── repository.ts     # Order data storage\n│   ├── inventory/\n│   │   ├── service.ts        # Stock reservation logic\n│   │   └── repository.ts     # Inventory data storage\n│   ├── billing/\n│   │   ├── service.ts        # Payment processing\n│   │   └── calculator.ts     # Price calculation with discounts/tax\n│   ├── notifications/\n│   │   └── service.ts        # Order notification templates\n│   └── index.ts              # Main entry point (exports)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── orders.test.ts        # OrderService + OrderRepository tests\n│   ├── billing.test.ts       # BillingService + price calculator tests\n│   ├── inventory.test.ts     # InventoryService tests\n│   ├── notifications.test.ts # NotificationService tests\n│   └── events.test.ts        # EventBus tests\n├── Configuration Files\n│   ├── package.json\n│   ├── tsconfig.json\n│   ├── vitest.config.ts\n│   ├── .eslintrc.cjs\n│   └── TASK.md\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Package.json Configuration\n\n**Name:** bench-debug-nightmare  \n**Type:** module (ES modules)  \n**Version:** 1.0.0  \n**Description:** Event-driven order processing system — hard debugging benchmark\n\n**Scripts:**\n- `npm run build` → Compiles TypeScript with `tsc`\n- `npm run lint` → Lints `src/` and `tests/` directories\n- `npm test` → Runs tests with `vitest run`\n\n**DevDependencies:**\n- typescript: ^5.4.0\n- vitest: ^2.0.0\n- eslint: ^8.56.0\n- @typescript-eslint/parser: ^7.0.0\n- @typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin: ^7.0.0\n\n---\n\n### 3. TypeScript Configuration (tsconfig.json)\n\n- **Target:** ES2022\n- **Module System:** Node16\n- **Output:** ./dist/\n- **Root:** ./src/\n- **Strict Mode:** Enabled\n- **Features:** ES Module interop, source maps, type declarations with maps\n- **Includes:** All src/**/* files\n- **Excludes:** node_modules, dist, tests\n\n---\n\n### 4. ESLint Configuration (.eslintrc.cjs)\n\n- **Parser:** @typescript-eslint/parser\n- **Extends:** ESLint recommended + TypeScript recommended\n- **Key Rule:** `@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars` with `_` prefix exemption\n- **Environment:** Node.js with ES2022 features\n\n---\n\n### 5. Vitest Configuration (vitest.config.ts)\n\n- **Globals:** Enabled (describe, it, expect available globally)\n- **Test Timeout:** 10 seconds per test\n\n---\n\n### 6. All Source Files and Exports\n\n#### **src/index.ts** (Main Entry Point)\nExports:\n- `EventBus` class\n- `ORDER_EVENTS` constant\n- Event type interfaces: `OrderEvent`, `OrderCreatedEvent`, `OrderCancelledEvent`, `OrderRefundedEvent`, `PaymentChargedEvent`, `StockReservedEvent`\n- `OrderRepository`, `Order`, `OrderItem`, `OrderStatus`, `OrderService`\n- `InventoryRepository`, `StockRecord`, `InventoryService`\n- `BillingService`, `PaymentRecord`, `calculateOrderTotal`, `PriceBreakdown`\n- `NotificationService`, `NotificationRecord`\n\n#### **src/events/types.ts**\n**Interfaces:**\n- `OrderEvent` - Base event with orderId and timestamp\n- `OrderCreatedEvent` - Items, customerId\n- `OrderCancelledEvent` - reason\n- `OrderRefundedEvent` - amount\n- `PaymentChargedEvent` - amount, paymentMethod\n- `StockReservedEvent` - items array\n\n**Constants:**\n```typescript\nORDER_EVENTS = {\n  CREATED: 'order.created',\n  CONFIRMED: 'order.confirmed',\n  CANCELLED: 'order.cancelled',\n  REFUNDED: 'order.refunded',\n  PAYMENT_CHARGED: 'order.payment.charged',\n  STOCK_RESERVED: 'order.stock.reserved',\n  STOCK_RELEASED: 'order.stock.released',\n  NOTIFICATION_SENT: 'order.notification.sent',\n}\n```\n\n#### **src/events/bus.ts**\n**Class: EventBus**\n- Module-level global handler registry (shared across instances)\n- `on(event, handler)` - Register handler\n- `off(event, handler)` - Unregister handler\n- `emit(event, data)` - Emit event (async)\n- `clear()` - Clear all handlers\n\n#### **src/orders/repository.ts**\n**Interfaces:**\n- `OrderStatus` type: 'pending' | 'confirmed' | 'cancelled' | 'refunded'\n- `OrderItem` - productId, quantity, unitPrice\n- `Order` - Full order with id, customerId, items, status, total, discount, taxRate, timestamps, notes\n\n**Class: OrderRepository**\n- In-memory Map<string, Order> store\n- `create()` - Create order with copy\n- `findById()` - Get order by id\n- `update()` - Update with partial fields (preserves id, updatedAt)\n- `findByCustomer()` - Filter by customer\n- `findByStatus()` - Filter by status\n- `clear()` - Clear store\n\n#### **src/orders/service.ts**\n**Class: OrderService**\nConstructor: OrderRepository, EventBus, BillingService\n\nMethods:\n- `createOrder(id, customerId, items, discount, taxRate)` → Creates → emits CREATED → charges payment → emits CONFIRMED → returns Order\n- `cancelOrder(id, reason)` → Validates confirmed → emits CANCELLED → updates status\n- `refundOrder(id)` → Validates cancelled → checks 30-day refund window → issues refund\n- `getOrder(id)` → Fetch order\n- `getOrdersByCustomer(customerId)` → Fetch all for customer\n\n**Constant:** REFUND_WINDOW_DAYS = 30\n\n#### **src/inventory/repository.ts**\n**Interface:**\n- `StockRecord` - productId, available (qty), reserved (qty)\n\n**Class: InventoryRepository**\n- In-memory Map<string, StockRecord> store\n- `setStock(productId, available)` - Set available quantity\n- `getStock(productId)` - Get stock record\n- `reserve(productId, quantity)` - Reserve stock (decrement available, increment reserved) → returns boolean\n- `release(productId, quantity)` - Release reservation → returns boolean\n- `clear()` - Clear store\n\n#### **src/inventory/service.ts**\n**Class: InventoryService**\nConstructor: InventoryRepository, EventBus\n\nMethods:\n- `registerHandlers()` - Register CREATED and CANCELLED event handlers\n- `handleOrderCreated()` - Reserves stock for all items, emits STOCK_RESERVED, rolls back on failure\n- `handleOrderCancelled()` - Releases stock, checks status !== 'cancelled', emits STOCK_RELEASED\n- `setStock(productId, quantity)`\n- `getStock(productId)`\n\n#### **src/billing/calculator.ts**\n**Interface:**\n- `PriceBreakdown` - subtotal, discountAmount, taxAmount, total\n\n**Function: calculateOrderTotal(items, discountPercent, taxRate)**\n- Calculates subtotal (sum of quantity × unitPrice)\n- Applies percentage discount\n- Applies tax on discounted amount\n- Returns PriceBreakdown with all amounts rounded to 2 decimals\n\n#### **src/billing/service.ts**\n**Interface:**\n- `PaymentRecord` - orderId, amount, method, status ('charged'|'refunded'), processedAt\n\n**Class: BillingService**\nConstructor: EventBus, NotificationService\n\nMethods:\n- `registerHandlers()` - Register STOCK_RESERVED and REFUNDED event handlers\n- `handleStockReserved()` - Emits PAYMENT_CHARGED event\n- `chargePayment(orderId, items, discountPercent, taxRate, paymentMethod)` - Calculates total, creates PaymentRecord, sends confirmation notification\n- `handleRefund()` - Updates payment status to 'refunded', sends refund notice\n- `issueRefund(orderId, amount)` - Updates status, emits REFUNDED event\n- `getPayment(orderId)` - Fetch payment record\n- `clear()` - Clear payments\n\n#### **src/notifications/service.ts**\n**Interface:**\n- `NotificationRecord` - type, orderId, message, sentAt\n\n**Class: NotificationService**\nConstructor: Initializes template map with 3 templates\n- 'order.confirmed' → \"Your order {orderId} has been confirmed. Total: ${total}\"\n- 'order.cancelled' → \"Your order {orderId} has been cancelled. Reason: {reason}\"\n- 'order.refunded' → \"Your refund of ${amount} for order {orderId} has been processed.\"\n\nMethods:\n- `sendConfirmation(orderId, total)` - Sends confirmation with template substitution\n- `sendCancellation(orderId, reason)` - Sends cancellation notice\n- `sendRefundNotice(orderId, amount)` - Sends refund notification\n- `getSentNotifications()` - Returns copy of all sent records\n- `clear()` - Clear sent notifications\n\n---\n\n### 7. All Test Files (30 Visible Tests)\n\n#### **tests/events.test.ts** (5 tests)\nTests EventBus functionality:\n1. ✓ Emits events to registered handlers\n2. ✓ Supports multiple handlers for same event\n3. ✓ Does not fire handlers for different events\n4. ✓ Removes handlers with off()\n5. ✓ Clears all handlers\n\n#### **tests/orders.test.ts** (12 tests)\n**OrderService Tests (10):**\n1. ✓ Creates an order and confirms it (status=confirmed, total=55)\n2. ✓ Reserves stock when order is created (available=7, reserved=3)\n3. ✓ Cancels a confirmed order (status=cancelled)\n4. ✓ Releases stock when order is cancelled (available=10, reserved=0)\n5. ✓ Refuses to cancel a non-confirmed order (returns undefined)\n6. ✓ Refunds a cancelled order within 30 days (status=refunded)\n7. ✓ Allows refund on exactly day 30 (status=refunded)\n8. ✓ Rejects refund after 30-day window (throws error)\n\n**OrderRepository Tests (2):**\n9. ✓ Creates and retrieves an order\n10. ✓ Updates order preserves other fields\n11. ✓ Returns undefined for missing order\n12. ✓ Finds orders by customer (finds by customerId)\n\n#### **tests/billing.test.ts** (8 tests)\n**calculateOrderTotal Tests (4):**\n1. ✓ Calculates total with no discount or tax (100)\n2. ✓ Applies percentage discount before tax (97.2)\n3. ✓ Handles multiple items with discount and tax (130.86)\n4. ✓ Rounds correctly for penny-edge amounts (33.88)\n\n**BillingService Tests (4):**\n5. ✓ Charges payment and records it (amount=110, status=charged)\n6. ✓ Sends confirmation notification on charge (type=confirmation)\n7. ✓ Issues refund and updates payment status (status=refunded)\n8. ✓ Sends refund notification (refund type, includes amount)\n\n#### **tests/inventory.test.ts** (5 tests)\n1. ✓ Reserves stock on order.created (available=7, reserved=3)\n2. ✓ Throws when stock is insufficient (error: \"Insufficient stock\")\n3. ✓ Rolls back partial reservations on failure (SKU-1 available=10, reserved=0)\n4. ✓ Releases stock on order.cancelled (available=10, reserved=0)\n5. ✓ Reserves stock for concurrent orders independently (available=12, reserved=8)\n\n#### **tests/notifications.test.ts** (4 tests)\n1. ✓ Sends order confirmation (type=confirmation, contains orderId and amount)\n2. ✓ Sends cancellation notice (type=cancellation, contains reason)\n3. ✓ Sends refund notice (type=refund, contains amount)\n4. ✓ Tracks all sent notifications (length=3)\n\n---\n\n### 8. Key System Characteristics\n\n**Event-Driven Architecture:**\n- Central EventBus with global handler registry\n- 8 event types define the order lifecycle\n- Services register handlers to react to events\n- Async event emission with sequential handler execution\n\n**Order Lifecycle:**\n1. **Create** → order.created → inventory reserves stock → billing charges → order.confirmed\n2. **Cancel** → order.cancelled → inventory releases stock\n3. **Refund** → order.refunded (within 30-day window)\n\n**State